From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PersonalTutor <personal-tutor@example.local>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] api: mount the PersonalTutor router

Mounts ``personal_tutor.api.router`` under ``/api/v1/personal`` so
PersonalTutor's REST surface (domains, knowledge graph, profile,
diagnostics) is reachable through the unmodified DeepTutor server.

The import is guarded by a try/except so that a PersonalTutor packaging
problem cannot prevent the upstream API from booting — the endpoints
simply won't be available, with a single warning line.

Rebase notes
------------
On conflict, keep the single ``app.include_router(...)`` line that adds
the ``/api/v1/personal`` prefix. This patch adds exactly one import and
one include_router call.

Apply with:  git am patches/002-mount-personal-tutor-router.patch
---
 deeptutor/api/main.py | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/deeptutor/api/main.py b/deeptutor/api/main.py
index 1111111..3333333 100644
--- a/deeptutor/api/main.py
+++ b/deeptutor/api/main.py
@@ -422,4 +422,13 @@ app.include_router(quiz_judge.router, prefix="/api/v1", tags=["quiz-judge"])
 app.include_router(quiz_judge.router, prefix="/api/v1", tags=["quiz-judge"])
 
 
+# PersonalTutor extension router. Mounted best-effort so a PersonalTutor import
+# failure degrades gracefully (endpoints absent, upstream API still boots).
+try:
+    from personal_tutor.api.router import router as _personal_tutor_router
+
+    app.include_router(
+        _personal_tutor_router, prefix="/api/v1/personal", tags=["personal-tutor"]
+    )
+except Exception as _pt_exc:  # pragma: no cover
+    logging.getLogger(__name__).warning("PersonalTutor router not mounted: %s", _pt_exc)
+
 @app.get("/")
 async def root():
     return {"message": "Welcome to DeepTutor API"}
